    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generally refers to people who serve as objects for artists (especially painters and sculptors) to copy. May also refer to people employed in that profession, or people employed to display clothes or fashion.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046693/Merriam-Webster's Collegiate Dictionary [online] (1997-2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一般指擔任畫家或雕刻家等藝術家描摹對象的人。亦可指受雇從事此業者，或是受雇穿戴供展示之衣物或流行精品者。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst in het algemeen naar mensen die als object dienen voor kunstenaars (met name schilders en beeldhouwers). De term kan ook verwijzen naar mensen die dit voor hun beroep doen, of naar mensen die in dienst worden genomen om kleding of andere modeartikelen te dragen om deze te laten zien.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
